      <p class="pageHeading">Questions To Ask During An Interview</p>
     <p>
    A job interview isn't just an opportunity for the prospective company to ask you questions.  It's also a time for you to ask questions to determine if the job is a good fit for you.  It is a GREAT idea for you to at least mentally prepare your own list of questions for a job interview.
</p>
<p>
Believe it or not, many companies actually evaluate part of your overall  interview performance based on the questions you ask.  Listed below are some possible questions that you might consider asking. 
</p>
<ul>
 <li>What are the primary qualities needed to be successful in this position?</li>
    
 <li>What are the greatest challenges to becoming successful in this position?</li>
    
 <li>What type of career path does this position offer? </li>
 <li>What new skills / technologies can I learn here? </li>
 <li>Where does this position fit into the organizational structure?</li> 
 <li>How soon will you be making a hiring decision? </li>
 <li>Do you have any questions or concerns about my background, my qualifications, or anything I’ve told you so far?</li>
    
 <li>How did this position become available?</li> 
 <li>When can I start? </li>

</ul>


